No less than two persons have reportedly been killed during a clash between rival gangsters in the Idumota area of Lagos State.  According to Punch, the clash which started on Thursday evening degenerated into Friday morning leading to the death of the victims. It was gathered that clash involved hoodlums from Idumota, Balogun, Martins and Oluwole areas of Lagos Island. It also affected trading and other commercial activities on the Island on Friday. The hoodlums reportedly shot sporadically into different directions as they displayed assorted arms and ammunition. Some shops were also said to have been shut down but security agencies on ground assured market men and women to open their shops. But they only mounted positions to forestall any form of resurgence of violence or hoodlums returning to take advantage of the situation.  Source Violence that rocked #EndSARS protests across the country worsened on Tuesday with 43  protesters and six policemen losing their lives.   Protesters calling for the disbanding of the Special Anti-Robbery Squad of the Nigeria Police have been carrying out peaceful demonstrations across the country since October 8.   However,… In "Top Stories" At least five youths, belonging to a villainous group on the Lagos Island, were on Wednesday night shot dead along Ajah Road in a war of supremacy amongst the rival groups, thereby plunging the state into pandemonium and counter attacks. Our correspondent gathered that the deceased, along with other youths… In "News" Abuja - A man simply identified as Adam, was reportedly shot dead, while four others were injured during a clash between men of Osun State Security Network, otherwise known as Amotekun corps, and some suspected hoodlums in Osogbo. According to sources in the Balogun Agoro area, where the incident occurred,… In "Top Stories"